---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/prose.css';

export const prerender = true;

const lastUpdated = '7 May 2026';

const sections = [
  { id: 'collect', title: 'Personal information we collect' },
  { id: 'use', title: 'How we use your information' },
  { id: 'disclosure', title: 'Disclosure to third parties' },
  { id: 'subprocessors', title: 'Sub-processors' },
  { id: 'choices', title: 'Your choices and rights' },
  { id: 'retention', title: 'How long we retain it' },
  { id: 'security', title: 'How we secure it' },
  { id: 'children', title: "Children's privacy" },
  { id: 'california', title: 'California privacy rights (CCPA)' },
  { id: 'eea-uk', title: 'EEA, Switzerland, and UK rights (GDPR)' },
  { id: 'transfers', title: 'International transfers' },
  { id: 'changes', title: 'Changes to this policy' },
  { id: 'contact', title: 'Contact' },
];
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Christ Note"
  description="How Christ Note collects, uses, discloses, and protects your information."
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="prose-page">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="prose-head">
        <a class="back-link" href="/">← Back home</a>
        <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </header>

      <article class="prose">
        <p class="lede">
          Christ Note is built around scripture and silence — the same applies to your data. This page explains, in plain language, what we collect, how we use it, who we share it with, and the choices you have.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>[Legal entity name]</strong> ("Christ Note," "we," "us," or "our") provides the Christ Note iPhone application and the christnote.app website (together, the "Services"). This Privacy Policy applies when you use the Services as a consumer. By using the Services, you agree to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described below.
        </p>

        <nav class="toc" aria-label="Sections">
          <p class="toc-title">Sections</p>
          <ol>
            {sections.map((s, i) => (
              <li><a href={`#${s.id}`}><span class="num">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>{s.title}</a></li>
            ))}
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <!-- ============== 1 ============== -->
        <h2 id="collect"><span class="num">01</span>Personal information we collect</h2>

        <h3>Information you provide</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Account.</strong> When you create an account or sign in via <strong>Apple Sign-In</strong> or <strong>Google Sign-In</strong>, we receive your email address and basic profile fields (e.g. name) returned by the identity provider. Authentication is handled by <strong>Firebase Authentication</strong>.</li>
          <li><strong>Sermon and study content.</strong> When you record a homily, paste a YouTube link, photograph notes, or generate AI summaries, flashcards, quizzes, chats, or Bible study notes, we collect the resulting content. This includes <strong>audio recordings</strong>, <strong>transcripts</strong>, <strong>summaries</strong>, <strong>notes and highlights</strong>, and <strong>chat messages</strong> tied to your account.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment information.</strong> If you purchase Christ Note Pro, the transaction is processed by the <strong>Apple App Store</strong> and tracked by <strong>RevenueCat</strong>. We do not receive or store your payment card details.</li>
          <li><strong>Communications.</strong> If you contact support, we keep the message and any information you choose to include.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Device data.</strong> iOS version, app version, device model, language, and time zone.</li>
          <li><strong>Diagnostics.</strong> Crash logs and performance traces, used to keep the app working.</li>
          <li><strong>Usage data.</strong> Server-side counters of AI operations (per operation, per user, per day or per lifetime) used to enforce free-tier and abuse limits.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Information from third parties</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Identity providers.</strong> Apple and Google return the basic profile information you authorized.</li>
          <li><strong>Subscription provider.</strong> RevenueCat returns purchase and entitlement state for Christ Note Pro.</li>
          <li><strong>Attribution.</strong> Apple's <strong>SKAdNetwork 4.0</strong> sends anonymous, aggregated postbacks to our measurement partner <strong>AppsFlyer</strong> when you install Christ Note from a paid ad. No user-level identifier is shared with advertisers.</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- ============== 2 ============== -->
        <h2 id="use"><span class="num">02</span>How we use your information</h2>
        <p>We use the information described above to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide and operate the Services — sign-in, recording, transcription, AI summaries, Bible study tools, daily devotional, and library sync.</li>
          <li>Enforce free-tier and abuse limits (server-side quota counters).</li>
          <li>Process subscriptions and entitlement changes through RevenueCat.</li>
          <li>Diagnose crashes and improve performance.</li>
          <li>Measure the effectiveness of paid ad campaigns through Apple's privacy-preserving SKAdNetwork framework.</li>
          <li>Communicate with you about your account, security, and changes to the Services.</li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations and enforce our Terms of Use.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>Transcription happens on your device</strong> using <strong>WhisperKit</strong> (an Apple-CoreML port of OpenAI Whisper). Audio files are <strong>not</strong> sent off-device for transcription; only the resulting text is sent when you ask for an AI summary or other AI feature.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>We do not use your sermon content, transcripts, notes, or chat messages to train AI models</strong> — neither our own nor those of our sub-processors. OpenAI processes API requests under terms that exclude training by default.
        </p>

        <!-- ============== 3 ============== -->
        <h2 id="disclosure"><span class="num">03</span>Disclosure to third parties</h2>
        <p>We share information only with the categories of recipients listed below:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Service providers and sub-processors</strong> who help us deliver the Services (see Section 4).</li>
          <li><strong>Legal and regulatory authorities</strong> when required by law, valid legal process, or to protect rights, property, or safety.</li>
          <li><strong>Successor entities</strong> in the event of a merger, acquisition, financing, or sale of assets, subject to standard confidentiality obligations.</li>
          <li><strong>With your consent</strong>, where you have explicitly directed us to share information.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>We do not sell or rent your personal information.</strong> We do not share your sermons, recordings, transcripts, notes, or chat content with advertisers.</p>

        <!-- ============== 4 ============== -->
        <h2 id="subprocessors"><span class="num">04</span>Sub-processors</h2>
        <p>The following providers process information on our behalf:</p>

        <div class="prose-table">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Service</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Data processed</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Firebase Authentication (Google)</td><td>Sign-in and session management</td><td>Email, OAuth identifiers</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Cloud Firestore (Google)</td><td>Library storage — notes, transcripts, messages</td><td>Your library content</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Firebase Storage (Google)</td><td>Audio recording storage</td><td>Sermon audio binaries</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Firebase Cloud Functions (Google)</td><td>AI orchestration</td><td>Transcript and prompt text</td></tr>
              <tr><td>OpenAI</td><td>AI summaries, chat, flashcards, quizzes, Bible analysis</td><td>Transcript and prompt text</td></tr>
              <tr><td>RevenueCat</td><td>Subscription management</td><td>Purchase and entitlement records</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Superwall</td><td>Paywall presentation and experiments</td><td>Anonymous experiment events</td></tr>
              <tr><td>AppsFlyer</td><td>Install attribution measurement</td><td>SKAdNetwork postbacks (anonymous)</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Apple SKAdNetwork 4.0</td><td>Privacy-preserving ad attribution</td><td>Aggregated conversion values</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Apple App Store</td><td>Distribution and payments</td><td>Purchase records (Apple)</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p>Each sub-processor is bound by contract and applicable data-protection law to use the information only for the purposes listed above.</p>

        <!-- ============== 5 ============== -->
        <h2 id="choices"><span class="num">05</span>Your choices and rights</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>App Tracking Transparency (ATT).</strong> When you first launch Christ Note, iOS will ask whether you allow tracking. You can decline; the app works fully either way. Declining means we use only Apple's SKAdNetwork (no <strong>IDFA</strong>).</li>
          <li><strong>Sign out.</strong> You can sign out of the app at any time from Settings.</li>
          <li><strong>Account deletion.</strong> To delete your account and associated content, email <a href="mailto:hello@christnote.app">hello@christnote.app</a>. We will process the request within 30 days.</li>
          <li><strong>Data export.</strong> Email <a href="mailto:hello@christnote.app">hello@christnote.app</a> for a portable copy of your library content.</li>
          <li><strong>Promotional email.</strong> You may opt out of promotional email at any time using the unsubscribe link. You will continue to receive operational and transactional messages (e.g. receipts, security alerts).</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- ============== 6 ============== -->
        <h2 id="retention"><span class="num">06</span>How long we retain it</h2>
        <p>We retain personal information only as long as necessary to provide the Services and comply with our legal obligations.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Account data.</strong> Retained while your account is active. Deleted within 30 days of account deletion, except for fields we are required to keep for legal, accounting, or fraud-prevention reasons.</li>
          <li><strong>Library content.</strong> Retained while your account is active. Deleted on account deletion request.</li>
          <li><strong>Diagnostics.</strong> Retained for up to 90 days.</li>
          <li><strong>Subscription records.</strong> Retained as required by tax and accounting law (typically 7 years).</li>
          <li><strong>SKAdNetwork conversion data.</strong> Retained in aggregate form per Apple's framework defaults.</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- ============== 7 ============== -->
        <h2 id="security"><span class="num">07</span>How we secure it</h2>
        <p>
          We use industry-standard safeguards: HTTPS/TLS in transit, encryption at rest in Firebase, server-side Firestore security rules that deny access to anyone other than the signed-in owner, and least-privilege access controls for the small team that operates the Services. No system is perfectly secure; we cannot guarantee that information will not be accessed, disclosed, altered, or destroyed by breach of any of our physical, technical, or managerial safeguards.
        </p>

        <!-- ============== 8 ============== -->
        <h2 id="children"><span class="num">08</span>Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>
          The Services are not directed to children under 13 (or under 16 in the EEA and UK), and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us personal information, contact <a href="mailto:hello@christnote.app">hello@christnote.app</a> and we will delete it.
        </p>

        <!-- ============== 9 ============== -->
        <h2 id="california"><span class="num">09</span>California privacy rights (CCPA)</h2>
        <p>If you are a California resident, the California Consumer Privacy Act (as amended by the CPRA) gives you the following rights regarding the personal information we collect about you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Right to know.</strong> Request the categories and specific pieces of personal information we have collected about you.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to correct.</strong> Request that we correct inaccurate personal information.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to delete.</strong> Request that we delete personal information we have collected about you, subject to exceptions.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to opt out.</strong> We do not sell or share personal information for cross-context behavioral advertising. There is no opt-out to exercise.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to non-discrimination.</strong> We will not discriminate against you for exercising any of these rights.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, email <a href="mailto:hello@christnote.app">hello@christnote.app</a> with the subject "California Privacy Request." We may need to verify your identity before responding.</p>

        <!-- ============== 10 ============== -->
        <h2 id="eea-uk"><span class="num">10</span>EEA, Switzerland, and UK rights (GDPR)</h2>
        <p>If you are located in the European Economic Area, Switzerland, or the United Kingdom, the GDPR (or its UK equivalent) gives you the following rights:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access, correct, or erase your personal data;</li>
          <li>Restrict or object to certain processing;</li>
          <li>Receive a portable copy of your data;</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent;</li>
          <li>Lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The legal bases on which we process personal data are: <strong>contractual necessity</strong> (operating your account and the Services), <strong>legitimate interests</strong> (security, abuse prevention, performance measurement), <strong>consent</strong> (where required, e.g. ATT), and <strong>legal obligation</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          The data controller is <strong>[Legal entity name]</strong>. To exercise your rights, email <a href="mailto:hello@christnote.app">hello@christnote.app</a>.
        </p>

        <!-- ============== 11 ============== -->
        <h2 id="transfers"><span class="num">11</span>International transfers</h2>
        <p>
          The Services are operated in the United States. Data is processed in <strong>us-central1</strong> (Firebase Cloud Functions region) and may be processed by sub-processors in the United States and elsewhere. Where required, transfers from the EEA, UK, or Switzerland are governed by the European Commission's Standard Contractual Clauses or equivalent legal mechanisms.
        </p>

        <!-- ============== 12 ============== -->
        <h2 id="changes"><span class="num">12</span>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top reflects the most recent revision. Material changes will be highlighted in-app or by email before they take effect.
        </p>

        <!-- ============== 13 ============== -->
        <h2 id="contact"><span class="num">13</span>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions, corrections, or rights requests:<br />
          <strong>[Legal entity name]</strong><br />
          <a href="mailto:hello@christnote.app">hello@christnote.app</a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
